text for its 1818 republication in light of Morris' work. It also demonstrates the profound influence of Jonathan Edwards (1703–1758) on Ryland’s biographical approach. While Edwards’s influence on Ryland and Fuller is widely known, this volume shows how Edwards’s biographical work, especially that of David Brainerd, influenced Ryland’s aim to promote “pure and undefiled religion” through recounting the life of his friend.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Nov 2021) 4aAndrew Fuller. 4aBaptisten. 4aBiographie. 4aJonathan Edwards. 7aRELIGION / Christianity / History.2bisacsh  aAndrew Fuller.  aBaptists.  aJonathan Edwards.  abiography.1 aGriffith, Christopher Ryan, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt0 cEPUBz97831106356140 cprintz978311063324540uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311063477840uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110634778423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783110634778/original  aEBA_CL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK